Class Provider

java.lang.Object
com.prototype.model.entities.Provider
@Entity public class Provider extends Object
Entity representing an equipment provider registered within the system.

A provider supplies technological or biomedical equipment, and this entity stores its basic business information such as name, tax ID, contact email, and address.

Each provider may be associated with multiple Equipment instances, forming a one-to-many relationship.

    • Provider

      @Deprecated public Provider(Long id, String name, String taxId, String contact, String address)
      Deprecated.
      Deprecated full constructor including the ID.

      Retained for compatibility. New provider records should rely on the constructor where the ID is managed by the persistence layer.

      Parameters:
      id - provider ID
      name - provider's legal or commercial name
      taxId - provider's tax identification number
      contact - provider's contact email
      address - provider's address

    • Provider

      public Provider(String name, String taxId, String contact, String address)

      contact - contact email
